==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zetetic
<hw>Ze*tet"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to
seek: cf. F. <ets>z⟦eacute⟧t⟦eacute⟧tique</ets>.]</ety> <def>Seeking;
proceeding by inquiry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Zetetic method</b></col> <fld>(Math.)</fld>, <cd>the
method used for finding the value of unknown quantities by direct
search, in investigation, or in the solution of problems.</cd>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Hutton.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zetetic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Zetetic
<hw>Ze*tet"ic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A seeker; -- a name adopted by
some of the Pyrrhonists.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zetetics</ent>⟦br⟧
